<span class="header1">FINANCE</span>
<p>The occupations in this field are for people who are able to
investigate and are good with numbers. If you would like to work with
finances, these occupations might be for you.</p>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Accountant</span><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CH/1287.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Accountant" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>If you enjoy working with numbers, you might
become an accountant. An accountant is responsible for helping a
company make money. You might advise the company to buy or sell
stock, or you might prepare its taxes.  You would also keep careful
records so that it was possible to tell how much money the company
made and where this money was spent.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a bachelor's degree for an entry level
job. Most accountants are CPA's (Certified Public Accountants). To
become a CPA you must have a bachelor's degree. You must also pass
a written exam.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of accountants was
$71,550 in May 2019. </blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Statistician</span><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CH/C1618_03.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Statistician" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>As a statistician, you would gather and analyze information
in numbers. For example, Major League Baseball players have their
batting averages determined by statisticians. If you worked in a
business, you would look at certain numbers to see how well the
company was doing.  Is it in good shape? Numbers give the
statistician the answer.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need at least a bachelor's degree in
statistics or mathematics for this job.  To get a promotion, you
must have a master's degree or a Ph.D.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of statisticians was
$91,160 in May 2019. </blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Loan Officer</span><br />
	<img class="job_pic" src="/images/icons/CH/C506008.jpg"
width="100" height="100" border="0" alt="Loan Officer" />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>A loan officer works for a bank or lending
company. As a loan officer, you would help customers fill out loan
applications and make sure that the information on the application
is correct. You would then see if the people wanting the loan met
your company's guidelines for a loan. If so, you would help to
process the loan.  If not, you would help them to understand why
they did not get the loan.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Loan officers usually need a bachelor's degree
in finance, economics, or a related field. Previous banking,
lending, or sales experience is also highly valued by employers.
</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of loan officers was
$63,270 in May 2019. </blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

<span class="header1">MEDICAL</span>
<p>Health care is one area where business and science blend well.
The occupations in this field need people who are interested in the
physical well-being of others.</p>

<hr size="1" />

<span class="header2">Medical and Health Services
Manager</span><br />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>As a medical and health services manager, you
would be
responsible for the day-to-day running of a health care facility
such as a hospital, clinic or nursing home. You would be in charge of
hiring employees and budgeting money. You might also help to raise
money to keep the facility going. To do well in this job, you need
business skills.  You also need leadership and people
skills.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>You need a bachelor's degree for this job. This
degree might be in hospital or health administration or in public health. Many people in this field also have master's degrees. </blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of medical and health
service managers was $100,980 in May 2019. </blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Nursing Home
Director</span><br />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>As a nursing home director, you would make sure
that the building and equipment are kept in good condition.  You
would also make sure that the elderly people who live in the home
are well cared for. An important part of your duties would be to
oversee the employees who care for the elderly. Another important
duty is to run the home so that it earns a profit.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>Many people who work as health care
administrators, such as nursing home directors, must have a master's degree. Some health care
administrators have degrees in public health.  Others have a degree
in public administration.  Still others have a degree in business
administration.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of nursing home directors
was $100,980 in May 2019. </blockquote>

<hr size="1" />

	<span class="header2">Polysomnographic
Technologist or Medical Technologist</span><br />
	<span class="header3">Job Description</span>
	<blockquote>Polysomnographic technologists monitor
the activity of adults and children in sleep laboratories.
They observe patients, collect data, and take notes during
a sleep study. Then, they summarize the information for
a sleep physician, who makes a diagnosis and recommends
treatment. Technologists often assist patients in understanding and
adjusting to the recommended treatment.</blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Education</span>
	<blockquote>To be a certified polysomnographic technologist
you will need to complete an associate degree program with an
emphasis in polysomnography. </blockquote>
	<span class="header3">Salary</span>
	<blockquote>The median annual wage of polysomnographic
technologists or medical technologists was $53,120 in May 2019.
</blockquote>

